HEADWORD: Offcut
<hw>Off"cut`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>That
which is cut off.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Bookbinding)</fld> <def>A portion of the printed
sheet, in certain sizes of books, that is cut off before
folding.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>off-day</ent>⟦br⟧
